caption: Small shaded green space with play area for children. This garden was originally a square located in the heart of the residences built in the 1950s during the redevelopment of this entire district. It is then converted into a family garden, integrating the two existing rows of lime trees. The latter run along Rue du Figuier, whose name has been documented since the 13th century.* Previously called the Figuier-Fauconnier garden, since 2003 it has paid homage to Roger Priou known as “Priou-Valjean” (1912-1999), municipal councilor of Paris, former General Councilor of the Seine, resistance fighter who participated in the liberation of Paris in 1944.
Small, quiet and well-shaded square, well located at the entrance to the Marais district. Good for taking a break before or after a visit to the neighborhood.

Small square with two entrances overlooking rue du Figuier (not far from the Saint-Paul metro or metro: Pont-Marie) which has some games for children, some beautiful very green and bushy trees and what seems to be a beautiful track for children. to play bowls...! It has been very well laid out, compared to what it represented before and which had no fence or facilities... I put photos that give you a better idea of ​​what a beautiful little square it is!
